# Module Docs Alignment

- When work changes module boundaries, exports, runtime behavior, or architecture docs, run `audit-module-docs-alignment` before closing the task.
- Treat code as source of truth; docs must reflect current symbols, module names, and behavior.
- Flag stale or duplicated doc sections and propose a concrete split/cleanup map when needed.
- Include a short module coverage summary in task outcomes when docs are affected.
- Keep progress tracking lightweight: module status, next action, last update.
